educed efficacy of hydrocodone or development of withdrawal symptoms due to reduced plasma hydrocodone levels.', 'Metabolism', NULL, NULL, 'Major', NULL, 'DDInter', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/40916/', '[1] "Product Information. Zohydro ER (HYDROcodone)." Zogenix, Inc, San Diego, CA.[2] Hutchinson MR, Menelaou A, Foster DJ, Coller JK, Somogyi AA "CYP2D6 and CYP3A4 involvement in the primary oxidative metabolism of hydrocodone by human liver microsomes." Br J Clin Pharmacol 57 (2004): 287-97[3] Vizcaychipi MP, Walker S, Palazzo M "Serotonin syndrome triggered by tramadol." Br J Anaesth 99 (2007): 919[4] Das PK, Warkentin DI, Hewko R, Forrest DL "Serotonin syndrome after concomitant treatment with linezolid and meperidine." Clin Infect Dis 46 (2008): 264-5[5] Mittino D, Mula M, Monaco F "Serotonin syndrome associated with tramadol-sertraline coadministration." Clin Neuropharmacol 27 (2004): 150-1[6] Gillman PK "Possible serotonin syndrome with moclobemide and pethidine." Med J Aust 162 (1995): 554[7] Mason BJ, Blackburn KH "Possible serotonin syndrome associated with tramadol and sertraline coadministration." Ann Pharmacother 31 (1997): 175-7[8] Dougherty JA, Young H, Shafi T "Serotonin syndrome induced by amitriptyline, meperidine, and venlafaxine." Ann Pharmacother 36 (2002): 1647-1648[9] Kesavan S, Sobala GM "Serotonin syndrome with fluoxetine plus tramadol." J R Soc Med 92 (1999): 474-5[10] Insler SR, Kraenzler EJ, Licina MG, Savage RM, Starr NJ "Cardiac surgery in a patient taking monoamine oxidase inhibitors - an adverse fentanyl reaction." Anesth Analg 78 (1994): 593-7[11] Hansen TE, Dieter K, Keepers GA "Interaction of fluoxetine and pentazocine." Am J Psychiatry 147 (1990): 949-50[12] Noble WH, Baker A "MAO inhibitors and coronary artery surgery: a patient death." Can J Anaesth 39 (1992): 1061-6[13] Rang ST, Field J, Irving C "Serotonin toxicity caused by an interaction between fentanyl and paroxetine." Can J Anaesth 5